    {
        " family. As on all brass instruments, sound is produced when the players vibrating lips  cause the air column inside the instrument to vibrate. Nearly all trombones have a telescoping slide mechanism that varies the length of the instrument to change the pitch. Many modern trombone models also use a valve attachment to lower the pitch of the instrument. Variants such as the ": null
    },
