        ". The trombone doubled voice parts in sacred works, but there are also solo pieces written for trombone in the early 17th century.     When the sackbut returned to common use in England in the 18th century, Italian music was so influential that the instrument became known as the trombone ,  although in some countries the same name has been applied throughout its history, viz. Italian ": null
