        " was the first major composer to use the trombone in an opera overture,  Alceste , but he also used it in operas such as  Orfeo ed Euridice ,  Iphigénie en Tauride  and  Echo et Narcisse .     The construction of the trombone changed relatively little between the Baroque and Classical period. The most obvious change was in the bell, slightly more flared.     The first use of the trombone as an independent instrument in a symphony was in the Symphony in E by Swedish composer ": null
