        ". In other countries, the trio of two tenor trombones and one bass became standard by about the mid 19th century.     Trombonists were employed less by cathedrals and court orchestras and so were expected to provide their own instrument. Military musicians were provided with instruments, and instruments like the long F or E bass trombone remained in military use until around the ": null
    },
