    {
        "partial": "harmonic series partial"
    },
    {
        ". Tightening and loosening the lips will allow the player to bend the note up or down by a semitone without changing position, so a slightly out-of-position slide may be compensated for by ear.                  As with all brass instruments, progressive tightening of the lips and increased air pressure allow the player to move to different ": null
