        " in the ": null
    },
    {
        "harmonic series": "harmonic series"
    },
    {
        ". In the first position on a B trombone, the notes in the harmonic series begin with B 2 , F 3 , B 3 , D 4 , and F 4 .     F 4 marks the sixth partial, or the fifth overtone. Notes on the next partial, for example A 4 in first position, tend to be out of tune in regards to the twelve-tone ": null
    },
    {
        "equal temperament": "equal temperament"
    },
    {
        " scale. A 4 in particular, which is at the seventh partial is nearly always 31 cents, or about one third of a semitone, flat of the minor seventh. On the slide trombone, such deviations from ": null
    },
    {
        "intonation": "intonation"
